TI  - The Globalization of our Mental Maps: Evaluating the Geographic Scope of JIBS Coverage
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 675
EP  - 686
VL  - 25
IS  - 4
AB  - This article analyzes patterns of country coverage in the Journal of International Business Studies during the twenty-five years of its existence. The analysis shows a substantial expansion in the journal's geographic reach over the years, but also a somewhat narrow “mental map,” with many countries and areas receiving only minimal coverage. Explanations for country preferences among researchers are explored and implications for the future are discussed.
